        "body": "## Summary\r\nThis PR surfaces Codex rate-limit reset credits inside the CodexBar menu. It fetches from the `/wham/rate-limit-reset-credits` endpoint and seamlessly integrates the available reset count and its subsequent expiry into the `Usage` section, alongside existing metrics. \r\n\r\nThis addresses the missing visibility of rate-limit resets, resolving #1633.\r\n\r\n## Changes Implemented\r\n- **Core Models & Fetching:** Added `CodexRateLimitResetCreditsSnapshot` and utilized `CodexOAuthUsageFetcher` to perform the fetch with a custom ISO-8601 decoder for robust time parsing.\r\n- **Provider Pipeline:** Safely baked the fetch into `CodexProviderDescriptor` using sequential await handling to respect the codebase's concurrency guidelines (no sibling `async let` for optional fetches).\r\n- **UI Integration:** Rendered `CodexResetCreditsContent` within the usage block. It features an `HStack` displaying \"Limit Reset Credits\" and the available count, with an expiry indicator (\"Next expires...\") positioned discreetly below.\r\n- **User Preference Parity:** The expiry text natively responds to the user's `resetTimeDisplayStyle` (Absolute clock time vs. Countdown).\r\n- **CLI Parity:** Added the reset credit readout to the `codexbar usage` CLI command.\r\n\r\n## Commands Run\r\n- `make test` (Sharded swift tests passing)\r\n- `./Scripts/compile_and_run.sh --test` (Live bundle and UI runtime verification passing)\r\n\r\n## Screenshots / GIFs\r\n\r\n<img width=\"290\" height=\"358\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7c30671f-8940-4b84-84f7-50dfd292ed19\" />\r\n\r\n## References\r\nFixes https://github.com/steipete/CodexBar/issues/1633",
